{"key":"processedPost-8571048","value":{"id":8571048,"first":8562113,"last":26564450,"when":1214594244,"utime":"06/27/08 10:17 PM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br />since temp drop is one of the pinning initiators? <br /></blockquote><br /><br />Incorrect.&nbsp; Temp drop isn't a pinning trigger with coplandias.&nbsp; They fruit in the summer, just like cubes.&nbsp; They'll fruit at room temp, but if you have a way to get it a bit warmer, they'll do better.&nbsp; They prefer to fruit at around 80F.&nbsp; Keep your substrate thin too.&nbsp; I've seen poor performance from pan cyans on thick substrates.&nbsp; Keep it to 1 1/2\" thick, with only about 1/4\" thick casing layer applied at full colonization.<br />RR","title":"Re: Pan Cyan temp changes","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}